🎯 Core Idea (IMPORTANT)
👉 Dynatrace does NOT natively understand ML metrics
👉 You must push custom metrics + logs into Dynatrace

✅ Step 0: Setup Dynatrace Integration (dynakube file genration in dynatarce with approperiate permission get token)
✔ Install OneAgent on AKS (KServe)
kubectl create namespace dynatrace
kubectl apply -f dynatrace-operator.yaml
✅ Automatically monitors:
Pods
API latency
CPU / memory

✔ Get Dynatrace API Token
Settings → Integration → Dynatrace API → Generate Token

✅ Step 1: Push Custom Metrics to Dynatrace
Dynatrace uses Metrics API

✅ Python Helper (Reusable)
import requests

DT_API_URL = "https://<your-env>.live.dynatrace.com/api/v2/metrics/ingest"
DT_API_TOKEN = "your-token"

def push_metric(metric_name, value):
    headers = {
        "Authorization": f"Api-Token {DT_API_TOKEN}",
        "Content-Type": "text/plain"
    }

    payload = f"{metric_name} {value}"

    requests.post(DT_API_URL, data=payload, headers=headers)


✅ ✅ 1. Accuracy / Precision / Recall / F1
✔ Compute Metrics in Training or Inference

from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score

acc = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred)
prec = precision_score(y_true, y_pred)
rec = recall_score(y_true, y_pred)
f1 = f1_score(y_true, y_pred)

push_metric("ml.model.accuracy", acc)
push_metric("ml.model.precision", prec)
push_metric("ml.model.recall", rec)
push_metric("ml.model.f1", f1)

✅ In Dynatrace Dashboard
Create charts:
ml.model.accuracy
ml.model.precision
ml.model.recall
ml.model.f1

✅ Add alert:
accuracy < 0.85 → ALERT


✅ ✅ 2. Data Drift (MOST IMPORTANT)
✔ Idea:
Compare training vs production distributions

✅ Example (mean drift)
train_mean = 50
prod_mean = df["age"].mean()

drift = abs(train_mean - prod_mean)

push_metric("ml.data.drift.age", drift)
``

✅ ✅ 4. Schema Change Detection
✔ Compare schema (columns)

expected_cols = ["age", "salary", "city"]

incoming_cols = list(df.columns)

if expected_cols != incoming_cols:
    push_metric("ml.data.schema_mismatch", 1)
else:
    push_metric("ml.data.schema_mismatch", 0)
``

✅ Alert
schema_mismatch == 1 → CRITICAL ALERT

✅ ✅ 5. Feature Anomalies
✔ Detect outliers / anomalies

import numpy as np

z_score = np.abs((df["salary"] - df["salary"].mean()) / df["salary"].std())

anomaly_ratio = (z_score > 3).mean()

push_metric("ml.data.anomaly.salary", anomaly_ratio)

✅ Alert
anomaly_ratio > 0.1 → ALERT
